TOON_VERSION: 1.0
DOC_TYPE: PRODUCT_VISION
DOC_ID: printforge.product_vision
TITLE: Product Vision and Operating Concept

PROBLEM:
  Internal 3D print engineering teams usually end up operating across fragmented tools:
    - slicers for files
    - cloud drives for uploads
    - spreadsheets for print queues
    - chat apps for coordination
    - whiteboards for printer status
    - tribal knowledge for material selection
  This creates ambiguity, wasted machine time, duplicate effort, and poor traceability.

VISION:
  PrintForge Ops becomes the operational command center for additive manufacturing execution.
  It gives engineering teams one place to manage projects, managed file uploads, printer assignments, material selection, queue status, and accountability.

CORE USER TYPES:
  - admin
  - engineering lead
  - manufacturing engineer
  - printer operator
  - technician
  - designer
  - viewer or stakeholder

USER STORIES:
  - As an engineering lead, I want to see every active project, owner, due date, and current manufacturing state on one screen.
  - As a technician, I want to upload the latest .3mf file revision to a project and mark it as candidate, approved, or superseded.
  - As a printer operator, I want to assign a printer, material, layer profile, and start a build job without editing the master project metadata manually.
  - As an admin, I want to define internal printers, material catalogs, and role permissions.
  - As a stakeholder, I want dashboards showing utilization, throughput, and blockers without touching raw machine settings.

BUSINESS VALUE:
  - fewer lost files
  - fewer unowned projects
  - faster shift handoff
  - clearer engineering accountability
  - material standardization
  - better printer utilization
  - audit trail for who changed what
  - cleaner foundation for future automation and MES-lite workflows

PRIMARY MODULES:
  - Auth and Identity
  - Project Workspace
  - File Vault
  - Build Queue
  - Printer Fleet
  - Material Registry
  - Activity Feed
  - Dashboards and Reports
  - Admin Console

PROJECT OBJECT:
  Every project should answer:
    - what are we building
    - why are we building it
    - who owns it
    - what files drive it
    - what material is intended
    - what printer is intended
    - what state is it in
    - what is blocking it
    - what was printed already
    - what changed last

PRINCIPLES:
  - One source of truth for internal additive execution
  - File traceability over file chaos
  - Shop-floor clarity over PM jargon
  - Fast data entry over beautiful complexity
  - Simple first-run flows, deep power tools later
  - Extensible schema from day one
  - Real-time visibility by default

RECOMMENDED V1 NAVIGATION:
  - Overview
  - Projects
  - Build Queue
  - Printers
  - Materials
  - Files
  - Analytics
  - Admin

RECOMMENDED PROJECT DETAIL TABS:
  - Summary
  - Files
  - Builds
  - Materials
  - Comments
  - History
  - Blockers

V2 DIRECTIONS:
  - QR labels for projects and printer bays
  - machine health monitoring
  - print duration predictions
  - estimated cost by print
  - automatic material depletion forecasts
  - approval workflows for production release
  - customer-specific internal programs
  - maintenance schedules and downtime prediction
  - camera feeds and remote print room overview
  - lot traceability and print farm optimization

END_TOON